==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preëminence
<hw>Pre*⟦eum⟧m"i*nence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧⟦eacute⟧minence</ets>, L. <ets>praeeminentia</ets>. See
<er>Pre⟦eum⟧minent</er>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of being
pre⟦eum⟧minent; superiority in prominence or in excellence; distinction
above others in quality, rank, etc.; rarely, in a bad sense, superiority
or notoriety in evil; <as>as, <ex>pre⟦eum⟧minence</ex> in
honor</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>pre⟦eum⟧minence</qex> of Christianity to any other
religious scheme.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Painful <qex>pre⟦eum⟧minence</qex>! yourself to view⟦br⟧
Above life's weakness, and its comforts too.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Beneath the forehead's walled <qex>pre⟦eum⟧minence</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Lowell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preeminent</ent>⟦br⟧
